data.title: RSL: New Me-My Surnames, June 1999 Update
data.text:
June Update to RootsWeb Surname List

New and Modified Surnames starting with Me-My

- To learn more about the RSL, including how to access the full RSL which has

over 600,000 surnames (these postings are only the NEW or CHANGED names).

how to submit surnames, etc., send any message to RSL-...@rootsweb.com

or go to the URL http://rsl.rootsweb.com/cgi-bin/rslsql.cgi

- If your site doesn't receive all the postings in this series of updates,

please don't ask me to resend, just follow the directions below and order

a copy of the update from the fileserver. Note for juno.com users: Juno

refuses all messages over 61K, so if it refused the original message from

this series, it will also refuse any replacement copy you order. Please

complain to Juno, not to me: it's their policy, not mine.

- Write directly to the submitter if you would like to exchange information.

Match the nametag at the end of each surname to the submitters'

addresses immediately following the list of surnames.

Entries are formatted as follows:

Surname Date1 Date2 Migration Comments & nametag

Date1 is the earliest date for which the submitter has information.

Date2 is the most recent date. The migration shows where people

of this line lived during the period listed.

Abbreviations used are in a file named family.abbrev that can be

be obtained by sending the command "get family.abbrev" to

ROOTS-L...@rootsweb.com in a message with the subject line

"archive". Or see the URL:

http://www.rootsweb.com/roots-l/cabbrev2.html
